snippet.textDisplay: I mean, I guess it makes sense to not just have the adults sitting around for the whole show but having them immediately know about the keys feels like an odd narrative choice, the reason the stakes are so high in the comics was that they couldn't get help from any adults because you become incapable of remembering how they work once you're an adult. It made the focus on the kids and their relationships. Also they're already opening the Omega door? And staring directly into it? The eff? Looks beautiful though, a lot of effort has clearly been put into this and I'm excited to see what they do with the series
